Members of the Dortmund squad took to social media on Tuesday to post pictures of the team making their way to London ahead of the Champions League clash with Arsenal.

Dortmund go into the match at the Emirates on Wednesday night with a perfect Champions League record, having already secured their place in the last 16 of the competition.

And, despite the club's woeful Bundesliga form that has left Jurgen Klopp's side 16th in the table, the squad looked in high spirits as they set off on their travels.

