The Italian, who signed for the German outfit from Torino in the summer, was also pictured being greeted by Dortmund's mascot Emma the bee as he arrived at the airport.

Dortmund, coming off the back of a disappointing 2-2 draw with newly promoted Paderborn on Saturday, recorded a 2-0 win over Arsenal in the reverse fixture back in September.

The Germans pose a stern test for Arsene Wenger's side, who are yet to guarantee their progression form Group D after throwing away a three-goal lead to draw with Anderlecht in the last round of fixtures. 

